Description: The return of the Holy Family from Egypt accompanied by angels, with Christ pointing to a house before them; composition with an arched top, reduced from the large plate Engraving
Producer name: Print made by: Cornelis Galle I
Curator's comments: A small-size reduction from the larger plate; unlike that, this does not give the name of Paggi.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (43 cf) (reduced version)
Subjects: return of the holy family from egypt
